WEBVTT

00:03.420 --> 00:05.587
Okay. "Now holding sides of hearth
in position...

00:05.797 --> 00:09.091
...lower mantelpiece assembly
onto top tabs."

00:11.428 --> 00:14.304
Look at that, l built a fireplace
with my own two hands.

00:15.223 --> 00:16.557
You're so butch.

00:17.517 --> 00:19.560
Aw, l got a little paper cut.

00:19.728 --> 00:22.813
Of course you did.
You're hands are softer than veal.

00:24.524 --> 00:28.444
Oh, uh, before l forget, Saturday I'm planning
a Dungeons & Dragons night with the guys.

00:28.611 --> 00:31.113
That's how you're gonna spend
your Saturday night?

00:31.281 --> 00:34.283
-Come on, I hardly get a chance to play.
-You poor thing.

00:34.451 --> 00:36.744
Is having a real girlfriend
who has sex with you...

00:36.911 --> 00:39.288
...getting in the way
of your board games?

00:40.457 --> 00:42.124
A little bit, yeah.

00:43.877 --> 00:47.046
Oh, great, l've always wanted to play
Dungeons & Dragons.

00:47.213 --> 00:50.132
Oh, I'm sorry,
I should've mentioned this earlier.

00:50.341 --> 00:51.467
You're not invited.

00:53.928 --> 00:54.970
Why not?

00:55.138 --> 00:59.475
Amy, from time to time,
we men need to break free...

00:59.642 --> 01:05.814
...from the shackles of civility and get
in touch with our primal, animalistic selves.

01:06.316 --> 01:09.568
By rolling dice and playing make-believe
with little figurines?

01:09.736 --> 01:11.820
Like a bunch of savages.

01:13.990 --> 01:16.408
Saturday night?
But I've been working late all week.

01:16.576 --> 01:20.245
-That was gonna be our night.
-I have to go, we play as a group.

01:20.413 --> 01:23.499
And if l'm not there,
then everyone will blame you.

01:23.666 --> 01:27.419
They'll be all, "Bernadette ruined
everything. She's the worst."

01:29.005 --> 01:33.801
So you see, heh,
I have to play Dungeons & Dragons.

01:33.968 --> 01:35.803
For the marriage.

01:36.805 --> 01:38.680
You're an idiot.

01:39.891 --> 01:44.019
I'm your idiot. Forever.

01:44.521 --> 01:48.524
So listen, l know we talked about
getting a bite to eat in Silver Lake...

01:48.691 --> 01:51.193
...then seeing the Christmas lights
in Griffith Park...

01:51.402 --> 01:55.364
...but Leonard's talking about
a big D and D game at his place.

01:55.532 --> 01:57.950
Saturday night just went
from crazy to epic.

01:58.118 --> 01:59.159
RAJESH:
Woo-hoo!

02:26.312 --> 02:28.313
All right, Sheldon, to start our quest...

02:28.481 --> 02:30.858
...you need to open this Christmas gift
I got you.

02:31.025 --> 02:32.609
A Christmas gift?

02:32.777 --> 02:34.862
You know l don't enjoy Christmas.

02:36.030 --> 02:39.324
-What's wrong with Christmas?
-Oh, where to begin?

02:39.492 --> 02:44.329
Trees indoors.
Overuse of the words "'tis" and "'twas."

02:44.497 --> 02:47.124
And the absurd custom of one stocking.

02:47.292 --> 02:49.835
Everyone knows socks belong in pairs.

02:50.003 --> 02:54.089
-Who uses one sock?
-A pirate with a peg leg. Heh.

02:54.632 --> 02:56.466
Actually, that helps. Thank you.

02:57.635 --> 02:59.511
Would you just look inside?

03:00.555 --> 03:03.807
Oh, a scroll! I like scrolls.

03:04.475 --> 03:07.686
They're my third-favorite system
of transmitting the written word.

03:07.854 --> 03:10.397
After stone tablets and skywriting.

03:11.816 --> 03:15.944
"You have all been summoned to join
a thrilling Dungeons & Dragons adventure.

03:16.112 --> 03:19.573
Your quest begins in a secret
northern village of elves...

03:19.741 --> 03:21.158
...who have all been massacred."

03:21.326 --> 03:23.368
Ah! l like where this is headed.

03:24.162 --> 03:27.831
"Your task is to rescue their leader
from a dungeon of ogres."

03:27.999 --> 03:29.791
That's a saucy twist.

03:30.210 --> 03:32.628
"That leader's name: Santa Claus."

03:32.795 --> 03:34.880
No, no, no.

03:35.548 --> 03:38.217
It's actually "ho, ho, ho,"
but you'll get the hang of it.

03:39.427 --> 03:41.678
Thought it'd be fun to make
a holiday-themed quest.

03:41.846 --> 03:44.765
Fun? Mixing Dungeons & Dragons
with Christmas...

03:44.933 --> 03:48.352
...is like making a sandwich of grape jelly,
the best-tasting jelly...

03:48.519 --> 03:52.105
...and petroleum jelly,
the worst-tasting jelly.

03:53.274 --> 03:54.691
Okay, here we go.

03:54.859 --> 03:57.945
"You find yourselves in the smoking
remains of Santa's village.

03:58.112 --> 04:00.322
Clearly a great battle has taken place."

04:00.531 --> 04:03.700
Oh, man, the first monster I see,
I'm going to sneak up behind him...

04:03.868 --> 04:08.038
...whip out my wand
and shoot my magic all over his ass.

04:10.541 --> 04:13.293
Do you hear yourself
when you say these things?

04:14.921 --> 04:18.423
Okay, there are ogre tracks and
a trail of broken candy canes in the snow.

04:18.591 --> 04:19.716
Sheldon, what do you do?

04:19.884 --> 04:24.513
I signal my contempt for your cruel plan
to shove Christmas joy down my throat...

04:24.681 --> 04:27.015
...by making a gesture that says,
"Get a load of this guy."

04:27.183 --> 04:28.225
[RASPBERRlES]

04:29.560 --> 04:30.894
Fine, Howard, what do you do?

04:31.062 --> 04:36.942
I follow the ogre tracks,
checking for secret doors along the way.

04:37.110 --> 04:39.987
And you discover a secret door
leading to a dark corridor.

04:40.154 --> 04:43.407
Let's make a plan. Spellcasters in the back,
warriors in the front.

04:43.574 --> 04:48.203
Screw that noise, l'm going in.
Hang on, Santa, l'm coming for you.

04:49.247 --> 04:54.001
Okay. You run into a room full of weapons,
hit a trip wire.

04:56.087 --> 04:59.131
A cannon blows your face off.
You die, you're out of the game.

05:00.133 --> 05:02.092
What? A cannon?

05:02.260 --> 05:03.927
Am l really out of the game?

05:04.095 --> 05:05.762
Lucky.

05:06.681 --> 05:07.848
Okay, come on. Moving on.

05:08.016 --> 05:10.892
Wait, doesn't anyone have
a rod of resurrection?

05:11.102 --> 05:14.104
Because if you've got one, l need it bad.

05:15.982 --> 05:18.942
Get in here with your rod
and give it to me.

05:20.403 --> 05:23.822
Okay, you need to say these things
in your head before you say them out loud.

05:23.990 --> 05:25.032
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

05:26.409 --> 05:28.702
Hey, I don't mean to interrupt
your little game...

05:28.870 --> 05:33.957
...but l thought you'd like to see what
you're missing out on. So, ahem, Bernadette?

05:34.125 --> 05:35.459
[POP MUSlC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

05:39.714 --> 05:44.801
Bernadette's wearing leopard-print pumps
and a racktastic red dress from Forever 21 .

05:51.351 --> 05:54.019
And there's Amy showing
all kinds of ankle...

05:55.563 --> 05:59.024
...in an outfit I'm assuming
is from Forever 63.

06:00.818 --> 06:03.320
And I myself...

06:05.156 --> 06:09.451
...am wearing a little number that got me
out of two speeding tickets and jury duty.

06:10.787 --> 06:14.664
I know they're making a rhetorical point,
I just don't know what it is.

06:14.832 --> 06:16.583
See you, boys. We are going drinking.

06:16.751 --> 06:20.170
Wait. Can l come with you?
My character died.

06:21.047 --> 06:24.925
-Sorry, Raj. lt's girls' night out.
-Maybe another time.

06:27.595 --> 06:28.804
Okay.

06:29.305 --> 06:30.347
Come on.

06:30.515 --> 06:31.807
[RAJESH GASPS]

06:31.974 --> 06:35.018
Girls' night. Girls' night. Ooh! Ooh!

06:38.481 --> 06:40.315
How does he not hear that?

06:42.902 --> 06:45.404
What's the plan?
We gonna teach our fellas a lesson...

06:45.571 --> 06:48.740
...by getting stinking drunk,
luring strange men into the bathroom...

06:48.908 --> 06:51.284
...and turning the toilet stall
into a temple of the senses?

06:51.452 --> 06:52.536
[POP MUSlC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

06:52.703 --> 06:53.954
-No.
-No.

06:54.122 --> 06:57.874
Jeez. Who's Forever 63 now?

06:58.876 --> 07:03.380
Can we get another bottle of champagne
for the table? Don't worry, it's my treat.

07:03.548 --> 07:06.258
-Thanks.
-You should come to girls' night more often.

07:06.426 --> 07:10.262
And not just because if you weren't here
this would be a can of Pabst.

07:10.430 --> 07:13.557
Nothing makes me happier
than the chance to spoil a lady.

07:13.724 --> 07:16.852
Just ask my dog. My vet says
if l give her any more foie gras...

07:17.019 --> 07:19.271
...she's going to die of gout.

07:20.398 --> 07:23.817
-Hey, let's help Raj meet a girl tonight.
-No, no, no, I'm fine.

07:23.985 --> 07:27.654
Are we talking one-night stand
or do we wanna get him into a relationship?

07:27.822 --> 07:29.781
Let's get him laid.

07:30.992 --> 07:33.452
Stop it, you're ruining girls' night.

07:35.246 --> 07:38.915
Raj, you're a great guy, you're in a bar
full of single women. Let us help you.

07:39.083 --> 07:40.125
You're a real catch.

07:40.293 --> 07:43.628
You're shy, but that doesn't mean
you shouldn't have someone in your life.

07:43.796 --> 07:46.256
That's sweet of you,
but what can you do to help?

07:46.424 --> 07:50.302
We'll nose around, see if we can find
a nice girl and then introduce you.

07:50.470 --> 07:53.430
Okay. A couple of things.

07:53.598 --> 07:57.350
Don't tell them l come from money,
I want them to love me for me.

07:58.436 --> 08:01.104
They must be insanely hot.

08:02.190 --> 08:05.317
Like nines or 1 0s.

08:05.776 --> 08:07.152
Nines or 1 0s?

08:07.320 --> 08:11.615
Okay, an eight is acceptable if she's willing
to bring another eight to the hot tub.

08:12.450 --> 08:14.576
You'll take any woman
who'll have you, right?

08:14.785 --> 08:15.994
In a New Delhi minute.

08:18.956 --> 08:21.458
I don't remember you buying these
miniatures in my store.

08:21.626 --> 08:24.628
Oh, uh, yeah. l got them on Amazon.

08:25.046 --> 08:26.129
Sure. l get it.

08:26.297 --> 08:30.300
Why support a friend when you can support
a multinational conglomerate...

08:30.468 --> 08:33.136
...that is crushing the life
out of that friend?

08:33.846 --> 08:37.140
I know, but when l shop online
I can do it on the toilet.

08:37.892 --> 08:40.310
Have you seen my store?
The whole place is a toilet.

08:41.145 --> 08:43.230
-Can we please move this along?
LEONARD: Yeah, sorry.

08:43.397 --> 08:47.734
Uh, you come to the end of the tunnel
and find a large chest.

08:47.902 --> 08:53.073
What do you do? And Howard, do not say,
"l feel up the large chest."

08:53.699 --> 08:57.786
Excuse me, l'm a married man now.
I wasn't going to say anything so juvenile.

08:57.954 --> 09:01.581
-Great, what do you do?
-I walk up to the large chest...

09:01.749 --> 09:03.250
...bury my face in it and go:

09:03.417 --> 09:04.459
[BLUBBERS]

09:08.339 --> 09:09.589
I open the chest.

09:09.757 --> 09:12.551
It's locked, but suddenly the door
behind you slams shut...

09:12.718 --> 09:15.262
...and now the walls of the room
start closing in.

09:15.429 --> 09:19.140
That's not good. My character and l
both have claustrophobia.

09:19.350 --> 09:21.601
Glowing letters appear on the chest
that read:

09:21.769 --> 09:24.229
"lf squashed to death
you wish not to be...

09:24.397 --> 09:28.108
-...sing of Svaty Vaclav and his victory."
-Who the hell is Svaty Vaclav?

09:28.276 --> 09:31.152
-Walls are getting closer.
-Oh, boy. Happy place, happy place.

09:31.362 --> 09:34.239
Svaty Vaclav was the Duke of Bohemia.

09:34.407 --> 09:35.991
Ten seconds from getting crushed.

09:36.158 --> 09:38.076
-Nine. Eight.
-What are we supposed to do?

09:38.244 --> 09:39.995
-Seven. Six. Five.
SHELDON: Wait, wait.

09:40.162 --> 09:42.706
Svaty Vaclav is better known
as Good King Wenceslaus...

09:42.873 --> 09:45.208
-...from the Christmas carol.
-Never heard of it.

09:45.376 --> 09:48.128
Must be the one Christmas song
not written by a Jewish guy.

09:48.879 --> 09:51.590
-Three. Two.
-Somebody sing the damn song.

09:51.882 --> 09:55.176
[SlNGlNG] Good King Wenceslas looked out
On the feast of Stephen

09:55.344 --> 09:59.222
When the snow lay round about
Deep and crisp and even

09:59.390 --> 10:00.557
Walls are getting slower.

10:00.725 --> 10:04.102
[SINGIN¤] Brightly shone the moon that night
Though the frost was cruel

10:04.270 --> 10:09.065
When a poor man came in sight
Gath'ring winter fuel

10:13.237 --> 10:16.364
-The walls stop. You're safe.
-That was amazing, Sheldon.

10:16.532 --> 10:17.991
-How'd you know that?
-Simple.

10:18.159 --> 10:21.119
I combined a well-known historical fact
about Bohemia...

10:21.287 --> 10:24.164
...with the memory of my grandparents,
Mee-Maw and Pop-Pop...

10:24.332 --> 10:26.833
...singing carols,
while l sat in front of the fire...

10:27.001 --> 10:30.337
...and tried to build a high-energy particle
accelerator out of Legos.

10:31.255 --> 10:34.924
-Okay, continuing our quest--
-Wait, there's still four more verses.

10:35.092 --> 10:36.760
You don't sing a song and not finish it.

10:36.927 --> 10:40.430
[SINGIN¤] Hither, page, and stand by me
If thou know'st it, telling

10:40.598 --> 10:44.059
Yonder peasant, who is he?
Where and what his dwelling?

10:44.226 --> 10:47.312
Brightly shone the moon that night
Though the frost was....

10:51.817 --> 10:52.859
[POP MUSlC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

10:54.153 --> 10:56.738
-It looks like he's doing pretty good.
-Of course he is.

10:56.906 --> 11:00.283
That girl just got dumped by her boyfriend,
she's angry, she's drunk...

11:00.451 --> 11:03.495
...and her favorite movie
is Slumdog Millionaire.

11:03.913 --> 11:05.830
That is some low-hanging fruit.

11:07.166 --> 11:08.625
Oh, here he comes.

11:08.793 --> 11:10.543
-So, how'd it go?
-Great.

11:10.711 --> 11:13.797
I bought her a couple of drinks
and she gave me her e-mail address.

11:13.964 --> 11:16.007
BOTH:
Ooh!

11:16.175 --> 11:20.637
"Jennifer at not even if you were
the last guy on Earth dot loser."

11:21.722 --> 11:22.764
What?

11:22.932 --> 11:24.224
I'm sorry, Raj.

11:24.392 --> 11:26.434
Why can't l find someone?

11:26.602 --> 11:30.063
I'm smart, l've got a cool job
and my naturally bronzed complexion...

11:30.231 --> 11:33.692
...means I can pull off mustard yellow
in a way most guys can't.

11:34.443 --> 11:40.365
-Aw, honey, it's not you, it's them.
-No, it's not. She was too beautiful for me.

11:40.950 --> 11:42.867
-Why would you say that?
-It's true.

11:43.035 --> 11:46.621
I'm always attracted to women l can't have.
I do it all the time.

11:46.789 --> 11:48.748
I did the same thing with the two of you.

11:49.750 --> 11:52.460
The two of them? l don't understand.

11:53.421 --> 11:56.798
Well, uh, there was a time
when l had a thing for Penny.

11:56.966 --> 11:59.634
I thought she was into me too.
She got drunk and naked...

11:59.802 --> 12:03.972
...and climbed into bed with me.
But apparently, l misread those signals.

12:06.267 --> 12:08.184
And you liked Bernadette also?

12:08.352 --> 12:09.978
That was before Penny.

12:10.146 --> 12:14.649
I make it a rule to only fall for
one of my friends' girlfriends at a time.

12:14.817 --> 12:17.360
I'm very old-fashioned that way.

12:18.028 --> 12:23.950
So at, uh, some point,
you probably had a thing for me too.

12:25.202 --> 12:26.786
No. Not really.

12:29.957 --> 12:35.086
-Come on, Raj, not even a little bit?
-Not that I can think of.

12:36.756 --> 12:39.090
Think harder.

12:40.926 --> 12:44.053
Nope. I guess the heart wants
what the heart wants.

12:44.221 --> 12:47.974
Or in this case, doesn't. l mean, at all.

12:51.187 --> 12:52.437
What?

12:54.857 --> 13:00.153
[SlNGlNG] Ye who now will bless the poor
Shall yourselves find blessing

13:00.321 --> 13:01.362
Ba-da-bum!

13:04.283 --> 13:05.325
Done?

13:05.493 --> 13:08.119
I think the word you're looking for
is "bravo."

13:09.205 --> 13:13.875
Okay, you leave the room and find yourself
standing before a pool of melted snowmen.

13:14.043 --> 13:17.378
Melted snowmen? Are there carrots
and lumps of coal in the water?

13:17.546 --> 13:20.673
-Uh, what's the difference?
-It's a game of the imagination, Leonard.

13:20.841 --> 13:23.802
-Paint a picture.
-Fine. You leave the room and find yourself...

13:23.969 --> 13:27.931
...standing before a pool of melted snowmen.
There are carrots and coal in the water.

13:28.098 --> 13:31.518
Do we know what happened to the top hats
and the corncob pipes?

13:31.685 --> 13:35.104
-You see those too.
-Oh, it's like l'm really there.

13:37.691 --> 13:40.902
I gotta tell you,
this is the most holiday fun l've had...

13:41.070 --> 13:43.988
...since my therapist
changed my anxiety medication...

13:44.156 --> 13:46.783
...and I stopped caring about the blood
in my stool.

13:50.329 --> 13:52.247
Good story.

13:52.748 --> 13:56.626
-What're you drinking there? Little eggnog?
-Yes. ls there a problem?

13:56.794 --> 14:01.381
No, it's nice to see you enjoying
a holiday beverage. Pretty Christmasy.

14:01.549 --> 14:03.591
Since when is eggnog a Christmas drink?

14:04.426 --> 14:09.764
Eggs are available all year round.
I've been known to enjoy this poolside.

14:10.224 --> 14:13.184
Come on, Sheldon.
You know all the Christmas stories...

14:13.352 --> 14:16.396
...and the carols, you've got
an eggnog mustache going on there.

14:16.564 --> 14:19.274
Just admit it,
you're getting a little yuletide spirit.

14:19.441 --> 14:23.528
Don't be silly. Christmas is a bunch of
baloney created by the tinsel industry.

14:24.655 --> 14:26.531
Why is this so important to you?

14:26.740 --> 14:30.743
I had enough crappy Christmases as a kid.
I'm tired of you sucking the joy out of them.

14:31.412 --> 14:35.456
-What was so bad about them?
-I grew up in a house full of crazy academics.

14:35.624 --> 14:39.794
Instead of leaving Santa milk and cookies,
we had to leave him a research paper.

14:41.422 --> 14:45.633
And in the morning, you could tell he'd been
there because the paper would be graded.

14:46.969 --> 14:50.555
No wonder you love Christmas.
That sounds amazing.

14:50.723 --> 14:55.393
It wasn't amazing.
I got a C-minus four years in a row.

14:55.561 --> 14:58.062
I'm familiar with your work.
C-minus was your gift.

15:02.359 --> 15:05.820
Amy, l'm really sorry.
I didn't mean to upset you.

15:05.988 --> 15:10.158
It's fine. l'm used to being the girl
who never gets looked at twice.

15:10.326 --> 15:12.368
I didn't have my first kiss until l was 22.

15:12.536 --> 15:15.413
The guy only did it
so I'd give him back his insulin.

15:16.874 --> 15:18.333
[POP MUSlC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

15:18.500 --> 15:21.836
Sometimes the pancreas wants
what the pancreas wants.

15:23.380 --> 15:25.715
Forget it.
I don't expect you guys to understand.

15:25.883 --> 15:27.050
I understand.

15:27.217 --> 15:30.720
In seventh grade, l played spin-the-bottle
and it landed on Alina Shankar.

15:30.888 --> 15:35.183
She said if I came near her,
she would break the bottle and cut me.

15:35.351 --> 15:36.684
You think that's bad?

15:36.852 --> 15:41.064
In college, l passed out at a frat party
and woke up with more clothes on.

15:45.945 --> 15:49.405
Sometimes I get so lonely I sit
on my left hand until it goes numb...

15:49.573 --> 15:54.118
...then l put it in my right hand and pretend
I'm holding hands with another person.

15:54.954 --> 15:56.245
I do that too.

15:57.289 --> 16:00.500
Sometimes the left hand tries
to cop a feel.

16:01.335 --> 16:03.211
And I let it.

16:05.881 --> 16:10.009
It's kind of nice to talk to someone who
understands what it feels like to be alone.

16:10.177 --> 16:11.552
It is, isn't it?

16:11.720 --> 16:14.138
But you're not alone anymore.
Now you've got Sheldon.

16:14.306 --> 16:18.559
I do. And don't worry,
someday you'll have somebody too.

16:18.727 --> 16:23.648
Thank you. l hope she's half as lovely
and amazing as you are.

16:25.275 --> 16:26.567
Thank you, Rajesh.

16:27.444 --> 16:28.987
He wants me, l'm good. We can go.

16:31.782 --> 16:33.574
-Damn it.
PENNY: What?

16:33.742 --> 16:37.704
Now that l know she doesn't like me,
I'm kind of into her.

16:39.206 --> 16:44.836
All right, I think l cracked the code
to lower the drawbridge.

16:45.004 --> 16:46.212
HOWARD:
Great. Let's do it.

16:51.677 --> 16:53.261
[PLAYING JINGLE BELLS]

16:53.429 --> 16:54.721
The drawbridge is lowering.

17:01.311 --> 17:04.022
-My carpal tunnel's acting up.
-Play through the pain.

17:15.409 --> 17:17.201
You did it. The drawbridge is down.

17:17.369 --> 17:21.706
You cross the chasm
and find yourself in a small dungeon room.

17:21.874 --> 17:26.753
And in the corner, chained to the wall,
you see a bloodied and beaten Santa Claus.

17:26.920 --> 17:30.548
He says, "Ho, ho, help me."

17:30.716 --> 17:34.927
Yes, we found Santa. Christmas is saved.

17:35.095 --> 17:37.597
Don't ever tell my mother l said that.

17:39.016 --> 17:42.351
I take out my skeleton key
and run to Santa to unchain him.

17:42.519 --> 17:46.189
But first l cast a spell of paralysis
on Stuart and Howard.

17:46.356 --> 17:48.691
-What are you doing?
-Can't talk, you're paralyzed.

17:49.777 --> 17:52.862
I get right up in Santa's big, fat face
and say:

17:53.030 --> 17:57.533
"Well, well, well, Jolly old Saint Nick,
we meet again.

17:57.701 --> 18:02.121
I believe the last time we spoke was
in the Baybrook Mall in Galveston, Texas...

18:02.289 --> 18:04.457
...when l was 5 years old, isn't that right?"

18:04.625 --> 18:06.667
Okay.

18:06.835 --> 18:09.712
My mother dragged me there
and plopped me down on your lap...

18:09.880 --> 18:12.256
...and you asked me
what I wanted for Christmas.

18:12.424 --> 18:16.886
I told you my Pop-Pop, because
that was the year my grandfather died.

18:17.054 --> 18:19.430
I missed him and I wanted him back.

18:21.266 --> 18:22.809
This is weird, right?

18:25.437 --> 18:29.774
Pop-Pop was the only one in my family
who encouraged me to pursue science.

18:29.942 --> 18:31.943
But you didn't bring him back, did you?

18:32.111 --> 18:34.904
No. Instead, I got Lincoln Logs.

18:35.072 --> 18:38.407
Now, you can build a lot of neat things
out of Lincoln Logs...

18:38.575 --> 18:40.576
...but Pop-Pop ain't one of them.

18:40.744 --> 18:45.206
And now you're here asking me
for something. To save you.

18:45.374 --> 18:49.293
Well, sorry, Mr. Kringle.
But today's not your day.

18:49.461 --> 18:53.756
I'm leaving you here to rot
and I hope the ogres feast on your bones.

18:53.924 --> 18:57.343
I take the skeleton key,
toss it into the chasm...

18:57.511 --> 19:02.056
...and on the way out give Santa a swift kick
in his bowl full ofjelly.

19:04.476 --> 19:06.227
Okay.

19:06.395 --> 19:09.188
So Wolowitz and Stuart are paralyzed,
Santa's dead...

19:09.356 --> 19:12.483
...and I picked this over having sex
with my girlfriend.

19:28.167 --> 19:32.295
-Santa?
-Oh, hello, Sheldon.

19:32.462 --> 19:33.504
[BELLS JlNGLlNG]

19:33.672 --> 19:35.673
You should be asleep.

19:35.841 --> 19:38.801
Well, then you shouldn't have jingle bells
on your boots.

19:40.262 --> 19:42.054
I've been wanting to talk to you.

19:42.264 --> 19:46.475
I'm sorry I disappointed you
when you were a little boy.

19:48.562 --> 19:50.688
I can do a lot of magical things...

19:50.856 --> 19:55.484
...but unfortunately bringing
your Pop-Pop back isn't one of them.

19:57.321 --> 20:01.824
-I understand.
-But l do have something special for you.

20:02.993 --> 20:04.410
Close your eyes.

20:06.580 --> 20:08.915
Oh, I hope it's a train.

20:09.082 --> 20:12.168
Oh, it's better than a train.

20:13.212 --> 20:15.338
Two trains?

20:16.048 --> 20:17.089
Better.

20:17.299 --> 20:23.012
-I'm getting three trains.
-Okay, open them.

20:27.392 --> 20:31.854
This is for leaving me in the dungeon
to be eaten alive by ogres.

20:32.022 --> 20:34.190
Now, hang on. In my defense--

20:34.358 --> 20:37.193
Ho, ho, ho, you big dork.

20:38.028 --> 20:39.070
[GASPS]

21:09.977 --> 21:11.978
[English - US - SDH]
